      <li><b>ISBN:</b> 12345678910</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="text-content">
    <h3>Description</h3>
    <p>The Monocle Guide to Drinking & Dining is for anybody who enjoys food but can do without the foam, fuss and trickery
      it’s often served with. It’s more than just food that makes a great meal though: we also offer tips on how to host,
      where to source the best produce and how to handle the sharpest kitchen kit. Alongside reports on the freshest markets,
      shops and producers, we’ve been everywhere from Adelaide to Zürich to put together our rundown of the world’s must-visit
      restaurants. Eating and drinking well should be a daily ritual and our guide offers tips to get the most out of it,
      whether you’re just nipping out for a bite or entertaining guests. Hungry for more? Do tuck in.
      <br><br>Our 340-page guide
      features original photography and illustrations printed on a selection of great papers and bound with a linen cover.
      Published by Gestalten. Gestalten is a Berlin-based publisher and produces high-quality editions in an environmentally
      friendly and resource-efficient manner.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>



